            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "The Baby & Child Nutritionist",
            "title": "Charlotte Stirling-Reed",
            "content": "<p>“I’ve been absolutely loving using the doddl cutlery set with my family. It’s really helped my daughter to hone her skills around self-feeding with a spoon and fork. I love the fact that they are made for little hands and make the idea of self-feeding so much simpler. Ada really has come on leaps and bounds since using them and is now able to do the “scoop” action by herself. My son also loves using the knife and fork and is getting much better at his cutting skills. It’s great that they just need to push down and apply pressure to cut their foods and, again, that they are made with little hands in mind. Such a great way to help them to transition to adult cutlery!”</p>",
            "link_text": "Learn more about Charlotte's work here!",
            "link_url": "https://www.srnutrition.co.uk/about-charlotte/",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#212529",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_VQi4p6": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Ruth_Watts.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "start",
            "text_position": "place-self-center-end text-end",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "Health Visitor",
            "title": "Ruth Watts",
            "content": "<p>doddl is a product I used, and I rate so much. The cutlery was fantastic for weaning, and we still have it in the drawer now, it’s my daughter's favourite spoon for cereal and she’s nearly 6 years old. It was a great transition spoon from starting to wean and learning to use cutlery to moving onto cutlery designed for adults. I love shouting out products that I believe in. Parents are the most vulnerable consumer out there because they want what is best for their baby and that's because they care so much.  We’ve all been there. And I never want to be part of a market where I have anything to do with preying on the vulnerability of parents. That's why I don't recommend products unless I have used them and think they will add real value. doddl is definitely one of those.</p>",
            "link_text": "Visit Ruth on Instagram",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#f2f2f2",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#1a1a1a",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_B9fdD8": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/SZ.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-start-end text-end",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "Paediatric Feeding and Swallowing Specialist Speech Therapist",
            "title": "Stacey Zimmels",
            "content": "<p>“As a feeding specialist and a mother, I was so delighted to discover doddl cutlery after it was recommended by a friend. I was so fed up of buying cutlery that wasn’t working to support my baby with his self-feeding development. doddl cutlery was perfect for him and within days he had mastered the loaded spoon and was stabbing and eating with his fork. The perfectly designed handles are short and fat which makes them easy to grab and simple to bring to their mouth. My son loved eating at the family table with his doddl cutlery – he was participating in our family mealtimes before he was walking!”</p>",
            "link_text": "Learn more about Stacey's work here!",
            "link_url": "https://www.feedeatspeak.co.uk/about",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#212529",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
