        "image_F49P6n": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Katia_Balducci_BSc_MSc_RNutr_Registered_Nutritionist_in_Public_Health.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-start-end text-end",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "The Baby Nutritionist",
            "title": "Katia Balducci",
            "content": "<p>“The doddl baby feeding set has been such a lovely addition to our weaning journey.The 2-in-1 bowl is sturdy, well-designed, and sticks perfectly to the highchair tray.<br/><br/>The cutlery set fits beautifully in little hands, helping babies build independence and confidence with self-feeding. They are short and even though the handle is chunkier they are super light. I love how well it supports fine motor skill development and encourages proper grip from early on, key steps in learning to eat independently. <br/><br/>The carry case is another win for me: we take it everywhere! It keeps the cutlery clean, safe, and ready to use whether we’re out for a meal or travelling.<br/><br/>From a mum and a child nutritionist perspective, I really value products that make feeding fun, practical, and developmentally supportive and this set truly ticks all those boxes.”</p>",
            "link_text": "The Baby Nutritionist",
            "link_url": "https://www.thebabynutritionist.com",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#212529",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_aKbMBj": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Vanessa_Eisch_-_Occupational_Therapist.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "start",
            "text_position": "place-self-start-end text-end",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "Occupational Therapist",
            "title": "Vanessa Eisch",
            "content": "<p>\"As a pediatric occupational therapist and feeding specialist, I am always looking at new and innovative feeding products. I came across the doddl utensil set and recently tried it out with my 18 month old son. It’s an incredible design! The handle is a perfect combination of chunky yet light and short which promoted a comfortable and functional grasp for his little toddler hands. The bowl of the spoon is wide and flat which allows him to “shovel” and successfully scoop his food! He’s been more successful with this spoon than any we have tried before! I’m definitely recommending doddl to families that I serve and keeping it in my OT toolkit. Thanks for making such a thoughtful, well designed product!\"</p>",
            "link_text": "",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#212529",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_LNWEQA": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/christine-pollack-300x300.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-start text-start",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "Paediatric Occupational Therapist",
            "title": "Christine Pollack",
            "content": "<p>“I absolutely love doddl. It comes with a children’s fork, spoon & knife that are ergonomically designed to foster independent feeding while building motor skills. Each utensil has grip zones strategically placed making it easy for kids to maintain control and manoeuvre the utensils. The handles are designed to promote a mature grasp which helps with drawing and writing. This is the first cutlery set I’ve come across that includes a knife safely designed for introducing and practicing knife skills with kids allowing them to participate in making her own food.”</p>",
            "link_text": "Follow Christine on Instagram!",
            "link_url": "https://www.instagram.com/a.dose.of.ot/",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#212529",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_GNCggk": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Colleen_Sarrazin_M.S._CCC-SLP_Pediatric_Feeding_Therapist_and_Speech-Language_Pathologist_founder_of_BabbleBites_Blog.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "start",
            "text_position": "place-self-start text-start",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "Pediatric Feeding Therapist and Speech-Language Pathologist",
            "title": "Colleen Sarrazin",
            "content": "<p>“As a pediatric feeding therapist, I frequently have parents ask me for recommendations on feeding tools like forks and spoons. I wanted to<br/>share with you an awesome set that’s made by female founded and award-winning brand. It’s the doddl toddler spoon, fork and knife utensils set, which are perfect for 12 months and up.</p><p>I love that the prongs on the fork are stainless steel so your baby has more success with poking their food, causing less frustration and more interest in using utensils. The handles are also ergonomically designed to encourage a proper grip. These are perfect for helping to develop independent feeding skills. I also really love the unique design of the spoon bowl that’s narrower at the front so it’s not too wide for little mouths, as well as a tapered bowl shape to hold purees and more liquidy soups while still encouraging easy lip closure on the spoon.</p><p>The little knife is also perfect for getting your little one involved in the kitchen and building early skills for cutting food. It’s effective, while still being safe for your toddler to use independently.</p><p>Not to mention these toddler utensils are dishwasher safe and BPA phthalate and microplastic free.”</p>",
            "link_text": "BabbleBites",
            "link_url": "https://www.babblebites.com/",
            "background": "#ffffff",
